9.0%), as well as lower functional enzyme evenness (p = 0.007, Beta =
0.18, partial R2 = 12%), both adjusted for age, sex, and diet diversity 
(Fig. 2B-C). However, there was no significant difference between the 
two groups in terms of richness for taxonomical strain or functional 
enzyme data. No differences in microbiome diversities were found in 
adults with ADHD on psychostimulants compared to those not on 
psychostimulants. 
ANCOM-BC identified the strain Bacteroides stercoris CL09T03C01 to 
be significantly lower in children with ADHD on psychostimulant 
